Lab setup: Single-server K3s cluster on Ubuntu 24.04 - Kyle Wilson 3/8/26

Controller
1. Update system
2. Install curl/git
3. Install K3s server
4. Export kubeconfig
5. Verify node is Ready

KUBERNETES ON CONTROLLER
	
Always:
sudo apt update
	sudo apt upgrade -y

Install basic tools:
	sudo apt install curl git -y

Curl and run install script for K3S which will install  Kubernetes API server, scheduler, controller manager, container runtime, kubectl:
	curl -sfL https://get.k3s.io | sh -

Verify the install by using:
	sudo kubectl get nodes

obtain the worker join token used for worker join authentication:
	sudo cat /var/lib/rancher/k3s/server/node-token

Example output = K1075abcdef::server:123456789


INDIVIDUAL NODES

	sudo apt update
	sudo apt upgrade -y

NOTE: curl should be installed but if not "sudo apt install curl -y"

Join the nodes to the controller
	curl -sfL https://get.k3s.io | \
	K3S_URL=https://192.168.X.X:6443 \
	K3S_TOKEN=K1075abcdef::server:123456789 \
	sh -

Once nodes are joinded confirm on the controller with:
	sudo kubectl get nodes
	
Happy Kubernetesing!
